OL,3,CFour of Britain's richest family given
OL,4,Cprison sentences for exploiting
OL,5,Cservants
OL,7,FThe Hindujas were not found guilty of
OL,8,Fcharges of trafficking, on the grounds
OL,9,Fthe staff in part understood what they
OL,10,Fwere getting into.
OL,12,FThe family topped this year's Sunday
OL,13,FTimes Rich List of the United
OL,14,FKingdom's wealthiest people, with a
OL,15,Fnet worth of around #37.2 billion.
OL,17,FThey did not attend court, but a fifth
OL,18,Fdefendant - the family's business
OL,19,Fmanager Najib Ziazi - was present, and
OL,20,Freceived an 18-month suspended
OL,21,Fsentence.
